50|$|The IBM 350 drive had fifty 24 in <b>platters,</b> {{with a total}} {{capacity}} of five million 6-bit characters (3.75 megabytes). A single head assembly having two heads was used for {{access to all the}} <b>platters,</b> yielding an average access time of just under 1 second.|$|R
